    • Constructor Detail

      • BASS_BFX_DISTORTION

        public BASS_BFX_DISTORTION()
        Create an object that holds a null BASS_BFX_DISTORTION.
        The call isNull() on the object created will returns true.
          BASS_BFX_DISTORTION obj = new BASS_BFX_DISTORTION();
  (obj == null) <=> false
  obj.isNull() <=> true
        To creates a new BASS_BFX_DISTORTION, use the static "constructor" : 
          BASS_BFX_DISTORTION obj = BASS_BFX_DISTORTION.allocate();
        See Also:
        allocate()

        public static BASS_BFX_DISTORTION asBASS_BFX_DISTORTION(Pointer pointer)

        This view is valid only if the memory holded by the Pointer holds a BASS_BFX_DISTORTION object.
